クラス DPJArrayBoolean<region R>

java.lang.Object
  DPJRuntime.DPJArrayBoolean<region R>
型パラメータ:
R - The region of a cell of this DPJArrayBoolean
public class DPJArrayBoolean<region R>
extends java.lang.Object

The DPJArray class, specialized to boolean.

The DPJArrayBoolean class wraps and provides a "view" of an ordinary Java array of boolean. In addition to array-element access, the DPJArrayBoolean class supports the creation of a subarray, which is a contiguous slice of the original array. The subarray itself is a new DPJArrayBoolean object. Both the original DPJArrayBoolean and the subarray wrap the same underlying Java array.

A DPJArrayBoolean stores a start position (indexed into the underlying array) and a length. Accesses to the DPJArrayBoolean are translated into accesses into the underlying array, offset by the start position. They are bounds-checked against the length of the DPJArrayBoolean. For example: 

 // Create a Java array a of 10 boolean
 boolean[] a = new boolean[10];
 // Wrap a in a DPJArrayBoolean
 DPJArrayBoolean A = new DPJArrayBoolean(a);
 // Create a subarray of A
 DPJArrayBoolean B = A.subarray(5,2);
 // Store value 1 into position 5 of a
 B.put(0,1);
 // Error:  Out of bounds
 B.put(3,5);

subarray

public DPJArrayBoolean<R> subarray(int start,
                                   int length)
                            pure
Creates and returns a new DPJArrayBoolean starting at index start with length length that wraps the same underlying array as this DPJArrayBoolean. Index i of the new DPJArrayBoolean refers to the same cell of the underlying array as index start+i of this.

Throws ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException if the interval start,start+length-1] is not in bounds for this DPJArrayBoolean.

パラメータ:
start - Start index for the subarray
length - Length of the subarray
戻り値:
Subarray of this DPJArrayBoolean defined by start and length
